'''David Dixon Award''' is a four-yearly award given to the outstanding athlete of each [[Commonwealth Games]], based on their performance at the event, [[sportsmanship|fair play]], and overall contribution to their team's participation at the Commonwealth Games.
The award was introduced in the [[2002 Commonwealth Games]] in [[Manchester]] and is named after the former honorary secretary of the [[Commonwealth Games Federation]] for 17 years, [[David Dixon (administrator)|David Dixon]].
The David Dixon Award from the 2014 Commonwealth Games was awarded to Francesca 'Frankie' Jones, who represented Wales in rhythmic gymnastics and won five silver medals and one gold.
