{{Infobox GAA player | code= Hurling | sport = Hurling | image = | name = James Delea | irish = Séamus Ó Duilé | fullname = | feet = | inches = | nickname = | occupation = Brewery labourer | county = Cork | province = Munster | club = | clposition = | clubs = [[Blackrock GAA|Blackrock]] | clyears = | clapps(points) = | clcounty = | clprovince= | clallireland = | counties = [[Cork GAA|Cork]] | icposition = Forward | icyears = 1891-1897 | icapps(points) = | icprovince = 2 | icallireland = 2 | allstars = | clupdate = | icupdate = | birth_date = 1868 | birth_place=Wales | death_date = 10 July 1950 (aged 71) | death_place = [[Cork (city)|South Douglas Road, Cork]], Ireland }} '''James Delea''' (1868 - 10 July 1950) was an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[hurling|hurler]] who played as a forward for the [[Cork GAA|Cork]] senior team.
Delea made his first appearance for the team during the [[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship 1891|1891 championship]] and was a regular member of the starting seventeen until his retirement after the [[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship 1897|1897 championship]]. During that time he won two [[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|All-Ireland]] medals and two [[Munster Senior Hurling Championship|Munster]] medals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hoganstand.com/Cork/Profile.aspx|title=Cork GAA profile|publisher=Hogan Stand website|date=|accessdate=18 May 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://munster.gaa.ie/history/sh_teams/|title=Munster Senior Hurling Winners|publisher=Munster GAA website|date=|accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref>
At club level Delea won multiple [[Cork Senior Hurling Championship|county club championship]] medals with [[Blackrock GAA|Blackrock]].
